criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  patients with American Society of Anesthesiologists (ASA) grade I-II;

          -  patients with a body mass index (BMI) of 18 to 25 kg/m2;

          -  age between 18 to 75 years old

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  patients with central nervous system and mental diseases;

          -  patients with a medication history use of sedative, analgesic or antidepression drugs

          -  patients with sinus bradycardia or atrioventricular block grade II or greater;

          -  patients with severe visual or hearing impairment or who were unable to communicate.
